Job Description
Application Process










That job listing (159048) is no longer active.Please try a new job search. 





Share this job with a friend

(or yourself!)




















Step 1
Create a Profile & Apply
After you've found your desired position, create a candidate profile here and apply online. Feel free to apply for more than one job opportunity using your candidate profile.






Step 2
Application Review
We evaluate all applications based on overall experience, education and skill. If your profile best matches our needs for the job, you'll be contacted regarding next steps.Unfortunately due to the volume of applications we receive each day, we are unable to reach out personally to every candidate.





Step 3
Assessment Testing
Some of our roles require additional assessment testing. If this is a necessary step for your application process, a Comcast recruiter will contact you with instructions.







Step 4
Interview Process
The interview process typically begins with a phone call or videoconference interview. If it is determined that you are a potential match for the role, an in-person meeting will be scheduled. Your recruiter will guide you through the logistics of scheduling.





Step 5
Selection Notification
A recruiter will notify you if you have been selected for the position. If you aren't chosen, don't get discouraged. We have many open roles at Comcast – and one might be the right fit for you.





Step 6
Pre-Employment Checks
As a condition of employment, you will be required to successfully complete a pre-employment drug screening test, as well as a background check. Your recruiter will provide further instruction.







Step 7
Once your offer letter is signed and all pre-employment checks are completed, you are officially a Comcast employee. Your recruiter will explain all next steps and set you up with your manager to ensure you get off to the best start possible.
Welcome to Comcast!
NOTE: You have the option to create a "job agent" that will notify you by e-mail whenever a new job is posted that matches your job search criteria. You can also join the Comcast Talent Network and we will regularly notify you with all jobs that might be a fit for your skillset.
If you feel you need special accommodations during the recruitment or hiring process, please contact your recruiter or contact us.




 




I don't have time to search for a job; can I just send you my resume? 




            We do not review resumes without a submitted job application. You can, however, join the Comcast Talent Network. By joining you will receive periodic emails about newly opened positions that fit your skills and experience. Membership also means that our sourcing team may contact you directly when we think you may be a fit for an open role.
          





How do I know if a job is right for me? 



We do our best to provide as much information about our positions as possible. Read the job description and requirements carefully to determine if the job is a good fit before applying. For some of our positions, we have Realistic Job Preview videos available that will give you greater insight into the role. CLICK HERE to view all of our videos.





How can I improve my chances of standing out during the application process? 





Be vigilant. New jobs are added every day so check for new postings often or join our Talent Network to receive alerts about new job opportunities.
Be prepared. Make sure your resume is up to date and is tailored to the position or department you are applying for.
Write a cover letter. Take the time to write a meaningful cover letter since this will serve as your introduction to us and is your first chance to make an impression.
Be unique. Be sure that your resume emphasizes the skills that relate to the job you are applying for and remove any irrelevant information.
Optimize your resume with keywords. Comcast uses an Applicant Tracking System (ATS) that supports our recruiters in matching applicants with positions that fit the candidate's skill set. To ensure your resume is not overlooked by our ATS, make sure you align your experience with the keywords from the job description in your resume.







How can I manage my application(s) and profile? 




            You can upload your resume in a Word document, PDF or RTF file, which will pre-fill the application form for you. Once you have uploaded your resume, please review the information in your application to ensure it is correct.As you update items in your profile (such as education, job experience, skills, etc.), be sure to click on the "Transfer" button to save your information for future use.
          





Do I need a resume to apply? 




            You can create a profile with your contact information, education and work history and not apply to a specific position.ORYou can apply to a specific position by creating a profile with your contact information, education and work history. When you click "Apply" to an open position, you will be prompted to verify the information on your profile, and you may have to complete a questionnaire. Once you have completed verifying your information and answering any questions, click the "Send Application" button. You will receive a message that your application has been sent, as well as a confirmation email.
          





Why can't I attach my resume to my application? 




            If you have a resume, do not forget to attach it to your application. When uploading documents to your profile, be sure to remove any special characters (&, $, @) from the file name, as these will result in a formatting error message. Rename your document as one word and attach.
          





How can I manage my job search using the online system? 




            Search for openings under the Employment Opportunities tab and click on the "Job Search" link. Below are some tips to improve your search:
            
If you know the specific title of a position, enter it into the Keyword search box. For more targeted results, enter the title within quotation marks.
If you are doing a general search, you can narrow your search by Functional Role, State, Employment Type and Hierarchy Level.
If a particular position interests you, click the "Save Job" button to review it at a later time. You can access your saved jobs via the "Job Management" tab.

            If you have created a profile, you can also set up a Job Agent, which will send you email alerts about specific positions/areas that you identify. You can also join our Talent Network to receive alerts about new job opportunities.
          













Got a question? Check our FAQs or connect with @ComcastCareers.
We're always online.
































 





 
